name: Private family home Oostvoorne
description:
Are you looking for a house which holds enough space to accommodate your family ? Look no further! Our home offers the comfort you'll need for an enjoyable stay. The property is located within walking distance to the village and with several beaches to chose from you'll not be easily dissapointed. Children are very welcome.

The space
We want you to feel as comfortable as possible, therefore you're free to use anything in the house. In the pantry are 2 washing machines available for you to use and 1 dryer as well as 3 clothing racks.

The Kitchen offers 3 ovens, 1 microwave, 2 fridges and an induction cooking stove.

In the front of the house is the main sitting area with a smart TV including Netflix and Apple TV. There is also a fireplace in the unlikely event when it's cold in the evening. In addition there is a seperate fireplace behind the kitchen table, this operates on remote control and will certainly add to a warm and cosy athmospher
neighborhood_overview:
The village of Oostvoorne is a 5 minute walk and offers serveral shops for your daily needs including bakeries, local fish store, deli, winery and a butchers. There is also a variety of local restaurants to choose from.

A 5 minute walk to the other direction from our home you'll find yourself in the 'Mildenburg bos' which is a lovely wood where you might even spot some deer!
host_about:
We are the Jaspars family. We have  4 children  consisting of 3 boys and 1 girl. 
Our home is located in the beautifull village of Oostvoorne which is in the Westvoorne region. We love living in this area as it offers a lot of different (authentic ) beaches,  there is great nature to explore as well as a wide choice of (water)sports facilities.

name: "Vita Vivet" mooie Airbnb met zorg: Vlierboom
description:
Welkom in ‘s-Gravenzande bij onze Airbnb Vita Vivet! Wij willen mensen voor wie het niet zo eenvoudig is om op vakantie te gaan door lichamelijke problemen een vertrouwd verblijf bieden met zorg op maat. Wij kunnen u tijdens uw vakantie zorg bieden, zodat u zich alleen hoeft bezig te houden met genieten van een heerlijk omgeving en ontspanning.

The space
Bij Vita Vivet heeft elke gast een kamer met een eigen badkamer met toilet. Er staat een televisie en er is WiFi tot uw beschikking. De ruime keuken, huiskamer en tuin mag gebruikt worden tussen 16.30 uur en 10.00 uur. Op zondag kunt u ook tussen 10.00 uur en 16.30 uur gebruik maken van deze faciliteiten.
De huiskamer, keuken en tuin worden van maandag t/m zaterdag tussen 10.00 uur en 16.00 uur gebruikt door het Ontmoetingscentrum Onderdak. Zij bieden dagbesteding aan mensen met een vorm van dementie. De Airbnb heeft een eigen ingang. U zult tijdens uw verblijf geen overlast ondervinden van het OC Onderdak.
neighborhood_overview:
Vita Vivet ligt letterlijk om de hoek van het gezellige centrum van ‘s-Gravenzande. Het centrum is voor iedereen goed toegankelijk en biedt een ruime keuze aan leuke winkels en horeca zaken. Op het Marktplein is elke vrijdag een gevarieerde markt, en worden er regelmatig leuke festiviteiten georganiseerd. Op de gezellige terrassen is het goed toeven.

‘s-Gravenzande is onderdeel van de gemeente Westland, wereldwijd bekend om de kassen, de innovatieve glastuinbouw en de verse groenten, bloemen en planten die hier geteeld worden. In het Westland kun je op velerlei manieren een bezoekje brengen aan de kassen! Het bezoeken van het duingebied dat het Westland biedt is ook zeker de moeite waard! Het is een kilometers lang gebied met brede goed onderhouden stranden. Bij de strandpaviljoens kan je ook nog eens heerlijk eten en drinken. name: Unieke woning in prachtige en rustige omgeving
description:
Volledig vrijstaand, luxueus uitgevoerd en uiterst comfortabele woning met grote tuin, gelegen op een unieke locatie in recreatiegebied 'De Rottemeren'. Helemaal buiten en toch op slechts 20 min. van Rotterdam centrum.
Sfeervol en met zorg ingericht.

Een heerlijke plek om te relaxen of recreëren of om gewoon te genieten van de rust en de natuur. Ideaal voor gezinnen met kinderen, natuurgenieters en rustzoekers!

Let op: Max. 4 volwassenen.

The space
Bent u een gezin met kinderen en bent u met 5 personen, dan kunt een aanvraag doen voor een extra persoon. Dit kan alleen als het gaat om een kind, want er geldt een maximum van 4 volwassenen.

Er is parkeergelegenheid voor twee auto's op eigen terrein, afgesloten door een automatische houten poort.
In de knusse woonkamer bevindt zich een (gas) open haard en schuifpui naar de tuin en terras. De ronde eettafel is uitschuifbaar waardoor er tot 6 personen aan kunnen eten.
De
neighborhood_overview:
Midden in recreatiegebied de Rottemeren, grenzend aan Het Bergse Bos en direct aan het eeuwenoude riviertje De Rotte. Vlakbij ook het vogelrijke natuurgebied de Eendrachtspolder waar ook de internationale Willem Alexander (roei)baan ligt.

Rotterdam Centrum is slechts 20 minuten autorijden. Het grote, overdekte winkelcentrum Alexandrium ligt op 10 minuten rijden.

De omgeving is werkelijk ideaal om te wandelen of fietsen. Maar daarnaast kun je er varen, vissen, kanoën, zwemmen, zonnen, skaten, golfen, picknicken en meer!

De Zevenhuizerplas is op 5 minuten fietsen en heeft een heerlijk strand. In de zomer is er windsurfles en kun je er naast surfplanken ook sups huren. Aan de overkant van de plas is het strand en de boulevard van Nesselande en mogelijkheid om te waterskiën. In de koudere maanden kun je hier ook heerlijk wandelen. Er zijn diverse wandel- en fietsroutes om het gebied en haar prachtige natuur te ontdekken.

name: Sfeervolle woning in Spijkenisse
description:
Onze woning bevindt zich in een rustig gelegen mooie nieuwbouwwijk van Spijkenisse. Erg gunstig gelegen voor trips naar Rotterdam of richting de mooie stranden van Rockanje en Oostvoorne.

Het betreft een ruime sfeervolle woning welke hotel chique is ingericht en van alle gebruiksgemakken is voorzien.

We verwelkomen u in principe zelf maar zullen tijdens uw verblijf niet aanwezig zijn. Indien u vragen heeft of twijfels of gewoon even kennis wilt maken stuur dan gerust een bericht.
Tot snel!

The space
Huiskamer/keuken:
Via de hal komt u in de huiskamer terecht. Hier kunt u plaatsnemen aan de keukenbar waar u gezellig met elkaar kunt ontbijten of dineren. In de ruime keuken is een inductie kookplaat aanwezig net zoals een combi oven en een oven. De handleidingen liggen voor u gereed. De huiskamer is voorzien van een tv met gebruiksaanwijzing. Er is een tafel van 2,5 meter waar u gerust aan kunt werken.

neighborhood_overview:
De buurt is erg rustig en toch ook dicht bij het centrum van Spijkenisse.
Wandel lekker aan het karakteristieke haventje in de wijk of langs de maasboulevard met uitzicht over de Oude Maas.

Andere faciliteiten nabij gelegen zijn:
Zwembad, Het Rivierabad: 18 min. lopen 6 min. fietsen
Supermarkten en eetgelegenheden in het Centrum: 12 min. lopen en 3 min. fietsen.
Bioscoop Kinepolis 20 min. lopen en 6 min. fietsen

Wij kunnen u voorzien van leuke restaurant tips :-) aangezien wij al ons hele leven in de omgeving hebben gewoond.

Wilt u graag naar het centrum van Rotterdam dan is dit ongeveer 25 minuten rijden met de auto of metro. Ook bereikt u via de bus of met de metro de nabijgelegen stranden van Rockanje, Oostvoorne en Hoek van Holland of de leuke vestingsteden Brielle en Hellevoetsluis.

It’s a perfect place to explore Rotterdam and Schiedam. I’m well informed about practical issues and the best places to visit in de (surrounding) cities and as a great host I’m pleased to tell you about it.

The space
The studio is located on the first floor on the front the building and has a private acces. A 15 steps stairs takes you into the hallway. When you enter the studio, you’ll find an open kitchen with al facilities to make an easy dinner or an extensive breakfast. You’ll find a double bed (180 x 200) with a high-quality mattress and in the bathroom a rain shower, sink and toilet.

The studio is conveniently located: in a 3 min. walk you’re at the metro which takes you in 15 min. straight to the city

name: The Old School B&B Apartment
description:
The Old School Schiedam
Always wanted to sleep during class? The Old School is there for you.

We have opened a Bed & Breakfast apartment in Schiedam. Located on the first floor of a former school building, which dates back to 1900. The building is situated in a quiet residential area, only a 5-minute walk to the historical centre of Schiedam. The centre of Rotterdam is 20 minutes by public transport and 15 minutes by car. Our street has free parking. Breakfast on request (euro 7,50 p/p extra).

The space
The 70 m2 (720 ft2) apartment is fully furnished and equipped with cooking facilities, a fridge, two TVs and wifi. It has a living room with a sofa bank, a sleeping room with a large double bed and airco, a kitchen and a bathroom.

Guest access
We share the entrance with our guests but other than that they have total privacy.
neighborhood_overview: Schiedam is one of the historical towns of the Netherlands, with houses dating back to the 14th century. It is famous for its jenever distilleries and its stone tower wind mills that are largest in the world of its kind.

name: Seagoing tugboat hostel Elbe
description:
Unique location. Large ship with space for 30 people in cabins for 1, 2 or 4 people. Our overnight stays include breakfast.

A drink in the evening is no problem. Unfortunately we do not accept bachelor parties or groups looking for a party ship.

Drinks available at the bar. No parties.

Assisted service, always staff (volunteers) present.

You are allowed to bring your own food and non-alcoholic drinks

The space
The Elbe is a big seagoing tug, built in 1959, now a museumship. Everything on board is still in the atmosphere of the past. Washbasins with separate taps, old-fashioned but solid, completely original and with a unique atmosphere. Shared washrooms with separate showers

Guest access

name: vakantiechalet bij zee, duinen en bos max. 4 pers.
description:
LET OP : Boeken voor minimaal 2 nachten.

Dit vakantiechalet ligt aan de rand van het Staelduinse Bos, vlakbij zee, strand en duinen van Hoek van Holland en Westland. Steden als Den Haag, Rotterdam en Delft zijn eenvoudig en snel bereikbaar. Ook veel wandel- en fietsmogelijkheden.
Twee slaapkamers (1 x 2 en 2 x 1 persoons). Keuken is compleet ingericht. Er zijn TV, Wifi, zonnige tuin, terras, schuur, wasmachine/droger en parkeerplek.

The space
Huisdier toegestaan. Tuin is afsluitbaar en heeft overdekt terras. Tuinmeubelen aanwezig. Parkeren kan voor de deur.

Guest access
Alle ruimtes coronaproof. Desgewenst kan sleuteloverdracht contactloos plaatsvinden.

Other things to note
Toeristenbelasting bedraagt Euro 1,25 per persoon per nacht en wordt apart in rekening gebracht.
neighborhood_overview: Vanuit het chalet wandelt u zo het Staelduinse Bos in. Door de duinen fietst u eenvoudig naar Kijkduin, Den Haag of Scheveningen. Langs de altijd interessante Nieuwe Waterweg zit u in no-time in Maassluis en Rotterdam. En door het Westland heen is Delft ook maar 20 kilometer verwijderd. Overvaren kan in Maassluis en Hoek van Holland, dan liggen Brielle, Rockanje en Oostvoorne eigenlijk ook “om de hoek”. En dan is er natuurlijk het strand van Westland en Hoek van Holland.

neighborhood_overview: De woning ligt in het dorp ‘s-Gravenzande. Diverse restaurants, bars, supermarkten en winkels zijn te vinden binnen enkele minuten loopafstand.
host_about:
Samen met mijn man Steven hebben wij in 2017 ons fijne huis gekocht, destijds in gebruik als kerkje en in 1930 gebouwd. Na eerst getrouwd te zijn in ons eigen huis / kerk zijn we zijn gestart met het ontwikkelen van tekeningen en het aanvragen van vergunningen en een woonbestemming. 

Na een grote verbouwing hebben we ons huis eindelijk kunnen betrekken, inmiddels wonen we hier samen met onze twee zoontjes, één van 2 jaar en een de jongste van 2,5 maand. 

We reizen en ontdekken de wereld graag. Zijn gek op zeilen en genieten van mooie natuur. Op momenten dat wij niet in Nederland zijn, bieden wij graag ons huis aan om deze fijne plek te kunnen delen.

neighborhood_overview:
Schiedam is a historic municipality and city in South Holland. It has some very nice canals to walk or cruise around and is well known for having the tallest historical windmills in the world. And also for its production of well known gin such as the Ketel One brand. The gin production was the source of much of the wealth that built the city into what it is today.
Schiedam was first made into a village in the year 1230 when the local river, The Schie, had a dam built on it to protect it from the sea. The dam brought much trade to the area, due to goods being brought to, or transported from the area, to towns such as Leiden, Delft and Haarlem. The village quickly grew and in the year 1275 received a charter to become a city from the sister of William The 2nd. She also built a castle in the area that you can still see today.
In 1340 two other cities, Delft and Rotterdam built connections with the fast growing city. In the 1400’s Schiedam became a pilgrim city for those devoted

name: Apartment in centre of Rotterdam
description:
This bright comfortable one bedroom apartment with a architectural thouch has a true cosy feeling! It comfortably fits two and is centrally located on a quiet street, near everything you need! Shops, musea, transport, dining, bars and supermarket!
Take a look at the floorplan to save money.

The space
This 60m² apartment is uniquely located around the corner of Rotterdam's famous cultural street 'Witte de Withstraat' with restaurants, arts and little shops. It's a 5 min. walk to the shopping center, the musea, the park and a 5 min. walk to the river Maas. There is a small supermarket around the corner.
The apartment is nicely renewed in 2021. There is a balcony on the street side and one on the back side. The apartment is nicely furnished and has a warm cosy appeal. Wifi available (the most comprehensive internet package).
max 2 persons.
Non smoking

Checking in and out can be flexible, it depends on if there are new guests arriving

name: Charming, Cozy Rotterdam Center
description:
The space
Welcome to Rotterdam!

This appartment is excellently located on the Mathensserlaan in the city center. Within 10 minutes walking distance you can find the musea park, the Erasmus University and Rotterdam Central Station. The shopping center is located around the corner and many pubs and restaurants are present in this area too.

The apparmtent is fully equiped for long and short stay included Free WIFI. The appartment suits 2 persons. There is a living room with a fireplace, a kitchen,a conservatory, a bedroom and a small bathroom. The appartment is on the second floor so please note that you have to walk up 2 steep stairs. Have a look at the pictures if you would like to see more.

The total space is 90 square meters. It's possible to have breakfast (for extra charge) in the hotel next to the appartment. There is also a private car park available (for extra charge). The rental price includes cleaning 1 time per week!

name: Sunny garden apt in Kralingen/R'dam
description:
The space
Fully furnished light filled 3 rooms with balcony and garden (with sun!) in Kralingen Oost (east), Rotterdam's most desirable neighborhood. Excellent access to metro, tram & bus, shops & restaurants. Only 8 - 10 minute walk to Erasmus University and ONLY 1km from the center of Rotterdam (3 stops on the metro -about 4 minutes) to metro & train station "Blaak" . The Blaak is where the main public library is and where there is also the best fruit and vegetable market (Tuesdays and Saturdays) just about anywhere!. Kralingen was a village until 1895 and still feels like a village, very green with lots of trees, free standing homes and stately townhouses. The apartment has a nice entrance hall with space for bicycles. The living area that formerly was two rooms (dining & living room) is now one large room with a large desk and French doors that open onto balcony and garden. Bathroom has full bath/shower combination. The bright eat-in kitchen is parallel to t
host_location: New York, New York, United States
host_about:
This apartment is my "pied a terre" in Rotterdam acquired many years ago.  Kralingen, where the apartment is located, was a village until 1895(?) and still feels like a village even though it is only 1 kilometer from the heart of Rotterdam...such as the main public library,  the main fruit and vegetable market and the Hoogstraat (Highstreet or Main St.).

The nearby streets and houses are really lovely, lovely, lovely and very quaint...  Just thinking about taking a walk within a block or two from my apartment lifts my spirits even when I am not at home in Rotterdam.    Rotterdam  is constantly changing and is a great modern city.

It would be my pleasure to give you more info on Rotterdam and the Netherlands ... just let me know what your interests are!

name: Boatappartment with great view on river Maas 1-5p
description:
Enjoy Rotterdam the Rotterdam way. On a classic Amsterdam ferry (1911) in a comfortable apartment with sunny deck terrace, a view on the New Meuse and the Rotterdam skyline. Sleep tightly in the bow of the ship on the rhythm of the tide.

The space
Loftboat Rotterdam Kralingen is a former Amsterdam IJ-ferry dating from 1911. The boat was converted into a comfortable 55 m2 guest apartment (1-5 persons). There is a large, sunny private deck terrace with a view on the New Meuse and the Rotterdam skyline. The apartment has its own entrance and offers a great deal of privacy.

The salon is flooded with natural light. The kitchen is ready for cooking, and coffee and tea are present. The apartment has a work space, a wood-burning stove, TV, tuner/amplifier, CD/DVD player, an IPod connection and WiFi. All rooms have central heating.

There is bathroom with shower, a separate bedroom with a double bed and sleeping options for 3 in the salon.
neighborhood_overview: The ship is moored in the small harbour of the former Rotterdam water company, right next to its monumental watertower. De Esch is now a residential area, a mix of modern architecture and the old water company buildings.  At walking distance (2 minutes) there is a shopping centre with a supermarket, cafe Tomtom and restaurant De Watertoren (in the watertower).  Also in the area nearby are Erasmus University, business centre Rivium, Arboretum Trompenburg and a nature walking/jogging path along the New Meuse.
host_about:
I'm an entrepreneur in the leisure field in Rotterdam.
I like meeting people from all parts of the world.
I  enjoy travelling and checking out other B&B's abroad.
I can give my guests a lot of information about Rotterdam and its attractions.
I enjoy rebuilding classic boats in an authentic nautical style.

name: Open Space Studio Old Rotterdam
description:
On the first floor of a typical Dutch apartment block built in the 1930's, the studio is located in the "Oude Noord" of Rotterdam. Completely renovated few years ago, it now features a big open space with natural light pouring in from East and West.

The space
The studio consists of a big open space (of around 45 square meters), organized n a night area (East), with a small studio corner, a living/dining area (West), a fully equipped kitchen, one bathroom (with toilet, sink, shower with thermostatic mixer), a small service room with washing machine a balcony on the West side, overlooking the internal courtyard.
It has been fully renovated few years ago, and some more improvements are ongoing at this very moment.
The floors package is a 1930's wooden structure, therefore the acoustic insulation is not the top: I appreciate you acknowledging this aspect and always respect the quietness of the neighbors, both downstairs and upstairs.
The studio is rec
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood Oude Noord is situated just North from the city center. It is a residential area with all services (supermarkets, shops, workshops, restaurants, bars, ...)
host_about:
I am an architect and I am passionate about good architecture and ancient urban settlements. I fell in love with Bosa while making my final thesis project at the university: the design proposal was a minimal intervention to re-qualify the Temo river's banks in the old town. Few years later, I managed to acquire this old house right in the medieval city center, where I try to be every time I free myself from work.
Due to my work, I travel quite a bit, and lately I find myself eager to learn much more about different traditions and costumes (especially from Asia and the Far East... China, India and Vietnam, and more recently from Central America and the Caribbeans). I find it impressive how many things we can learn from each other cultures, and how much can be adapted and adjusted among different locations. I like this positive side of globalization, where intelligence becomes global and local traditions acquire value.
I am currently committed in a research aiming to drastically lower the construction cost (price per square meter) of social housing through implementation of sustainable practices: everybody should have the right to a comfortable home, in a cleaner world.
I am based in Rotterdam, The Netherlands, but I often engage in projects which bring me in beautiful places: I am currently living in Phoenix, Arizona.

name: Groepsverhuur Luciana en/of Catherina te Rotterdam
description:
Met max 22 slaapplaatsen per schip aan de rivier in hartje Rotterdam!
Dus niet max. 16 pers.
Aan het gezellig rustiek scheepvaartkwartier liggen onze boten in het zicht van een super skyline, nl. het "Manhattan aan de maas".
Inkoopcentrum en uitgaansgebieden zijn op loopafstand.
De snelle watertaxi komt voor de deur.
Rond oudejaarsavond geldt tenminste 4 nachten huur.
Let op! beide schepen staan op EEN agenda.
Dus ook al lijkt bv. een weekend bezet is het 2e schip nog vrij, altijd doorvragen!

The space
Beweegt omdat zij drijft.
Voorbij varende rijnschepen geven een wisselend uitzicht.
De ruime dekken zijn vrij toegankelijk en laten u ronddwalen.
Een grote BBQ staat tot jullie beschikking

Guest access
Per schip is plaats voor een gezelschap met max. 22 personen.
Alleen aan dek mag men roken.
U kan ook met een klein gezelschap boeken.
De huurprijs blijft echter gelijk.
Al
neighborhood_overview:
Het historisch scheepvaartkwartier is een mooi dorp in Rotterdam centrum.
Prachtige uitzichten, veel groen, fijn wandelen en uitgaan.
host_about:
Uw gastheer is familievader en voert als kapitein samen met vrouw en zonen de zeilrederij Vof Europe Sailing.
Ik woon met familie nabij de te verhuren zeilschepen 'Luciana', 'Catherina' en 'Marie Galant' in de Veerhaven op ons woon/vergaderschip de 'Schoneveld'.
Mijn favoriete reisbestemmingen zijn de te bezeilen landen als Noorwegen, Deense eilanden, Oost en Noordzeekusten en Gomera, La Palma en El Hierro.
Ik heb weinig tijd voor boeken, maar lees graag reisverhalen en (maritieme)geschiedenis.
Mijn vrouw en ik gaan graag met het hele gezin naar de bioscoop.
Ik ben graag gastheer en stel het op prijs vooraf met de klant overleg te voeren, kennis te maken en te peilen wat verlangd wordt.
Bij een verblijf op een schip gaat veiligheid voor alles en dus ben ik dag en nacht mobiel bereikbaar.
Mijn levensmotto is dat wat ik in werktijd mag doen mijn hobby is!

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is dynamic and international, offers many local (Asian) takeaways. It is the Asia of Rotterdam so to speak. Rotterdam is a highly diverse, global city with over 200 different nationalities. That's more than Amsterdam, to give you an idea.

The neighborhood is somewhat gritty chic and on first impression a little scruffy. It's not the Hamptons, far from it, but you'll see its soul by walking the streets. It lives, it moves, and people are helpful if you need directions or something.

There are two supermarkets around the corner, bakery's, liquor shop, two late-night shops, and a pharmacy. Near cafes, bars and restaurants and shopping center of Rotterdam, all by foot. Ask me for specific recommendations.

The apartment is about 5-10 minutes walking distance to the main hotspots and epicenter of Rotterdam.

a mere 30 minutes (door to door) to Ahoy, the best ESF location ever.

So much nicer to have your five star apartment in the city centre for good food, good cocktails and great nightlife!
See you in May:)

You can interact with people in the kitchen sitting at the big table in the living room. My kitchen has all the mod cons as well as a Nespresso machine.
You don't have to stay in the kitchen all the time, you can also ''chill'' on the couch : read one of the many (English) books!

O
neighborhood_overview:
Lonely Planet chose Rotterdam as the nr. 5 top city to visit in 2016!
Rubroek, my neighbourhood, is really the most fantastic place to live in Rotterdam. It's quiet (my house is opposite a little park and I overlook The Rotte. (a canal).
When you walk to the end of my street, you're aleady in the city centre: you can stop for a coffee at the Coffee Company on the Meent, have breakfast or eat the best apple pie in the world at Dudoc restaurant, eat an icecream at the IJssalon,(try the cherry mania!!), go to the lively Rotterdam market (on Tuesdays and Saturdays), go shopping in the Pannekoekstraat (Pancake-street) , see the many famous tourist attractions: Hotel New York, The Erasmusbridge, Blijdorp Zoo, the Harbour, the Doelen, The Schouwburg Theatre, The Kunsthal, Museum Boymans van Beuningen, the Market Hall.
Also take part in the many events the city has to offer: Poetry International, Hidden Gardens, CHIO, Parade, North Sea Jazz, World Ports Classics, Zig Zag Ci
host_about:
''It's better to travel hopefully than to arrive".
Yet, when living in Rotterdam, you don't have to travel a lot, because my hometown has everything a person needs:)
Apart from Rotterdam, my favourite cities are London, New York and Rome.
I've found my ''little piece of heaven'' in my apartment in the city of Rotterdam.
Close to everything I love:  my friends, my work, great restaurants, movie theatres, bookshops..
Great food is a passion of mine (although I'm not very good at cooking myself) and I go to the movies at least twice a month at Lantaarn/Venster, where independent movies are shown.

neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is a chic gem set in the east of Rotterdam. With an expansive backyard, where the rest of the city is always welcome for a barbecue: the Kralingse Bos.

The east of Rotterdam boasts the city’s biggest park: the Kralingse Bos. This green oasis is a major attraction for everyone seeking to flee the busy urban streets for some fresh air and peace and quiet. Not that it’s always quiet; the Kralingse Bos is often humming with pleasant activity on sunny weekend afternoons. Nature lovers enjoy a stroll through the forest. Sun-worshipers bask on the lake’s small beach. Toddlers splash around in the wading pool or play at the petting zoo. Bigger children will love exploring the climbing park. People rollerblade, jog and cycle to their heart’s content around the lake and go sailing on the lake, while snacks are served at tables on the waterfront terraces.

name: Family home with huge garden at the Riverside
description:
Our spacious (175m2) light and recently renovated house (2020) offers you best of both worlds: in the middle of nature, with the river 'de Rotte' right in front of our door, with a huge garden to enjoy the sun, but still close enough to reach the city centre by bicycle (12 min) or by foot (only 25 min). Even our Rotterdam friends envy us for this perfect spot! We rent out the house when we are out traveling ourselves, so it's fully equipped with everything you need!

The space
The full house is about 175 square meters and has four rooms upstairs: one bathroom, a kids room with a double kids bed, one ‘in between room’ and an attic with a kingsize bed. The attic is open with the ‘in between room’ and bathroom.

Our living room is open with the kitchen, has a fire place in the middle and a front door and a back door that leads to the balcony which is open to the garden. At the end of our garden you will enter our ‘landje’ (little land) where we have a play
neighborhood_overview: Nature and water. You'll see a lot of sports practiced here: running, biking, rowing, horse back riding. The people living here are a mix of young families and older friendly people.
host_about:
Together with my two boys, I live in one of the most beautiful parts of Rotterdam, at the river the Rotte. It always feels like holiday at home, surrounded by nature, and only 15 minutes (by bike!) from the citycentre.

We all love to travel, and meet new people. And next to traveling, photography is my passion and (lucky me!) profession. 
To combine both of these beautiful things in life makes me a real lucky and happy women! 

Before we bought this house we went traveling for 15 months all over the world, so we know that to really get to know a place, you have to meet and stay with the locals.
That is why we think AirBnB is a perfect medium, both as a guest ánd as a host!

name: Rotterdam's coolest apartment
description:
The best apartment... on the coolest street... in the greatest city... of the Netherlands!

The space
This very spacious apartment is located right in the middle of the Witte de Withstraat. A great street full of arty outdoor cafés, bars, restaurants and shops. Take a look at any guidebook; this is the place you definitely won’t want to miss. So, what could be better than booking an apartment on this very street! Within walking distance of everything, with public transport and parking just around the corner, and a supermarket across the street. You’ll have an instant good time!

Living room:
Very large and full of light. Fully equipped.

The stylishly furnished living room is very large, with windows stretching the full width. It's wonderful to sit in the windowsill and look outside. No matter how busy and lively the street gets down there, up here it’s remarkably quiet. It’s all here: super-fast internet, a brand-new TV, a record player w
neighborhood_overview:
The Witte de Withstraat is a very lively street in the city center, with cultural institutions, restaurants, galleries, cool shops, and bars.
The apartment is right in the middle, across from a former school building, which is now a museum/gallery space for modern art (Tent/Witte de With).

The street is on the so-called Art Axis (Kunst-as) between the museums on the Leuvehaven and the Museum Park (Boijmans Van Beuningen, Het Nieuwe Instituut, the Natural History Museum, and the Kunsthal). The park is a short walk from the apartment. Festivals and markets are held here all year round (including the Parade, Open Air Cinema, Swan Market, Museum Night, etc.).

New in town? There's no better place from which to discover Rotterdam than from this apartment. A must see.

description:

The space
Nice to meet you here! Our cats will not be at home during the Christmas holiday! Our apartment was build in 1933. This part of Rotterdam was not bombed during the 2nd world war. That's why you will see many characteristic houses here. It is situated in a decent neighbourhood.
We have a fully equipped kitchen, a living room with a big and comfortable sofa and flatscreen tv with netflix subscription, dinner table with 6 chairs, a beautiful wooden stair that leads to the upper floor. We have 2 piano's and a lot of children toys. We have 2 toilets and a modern bathroom with bath tub and a separate shower.
Please treat

Verder besteed ik graag veel tijd aan surfen, mijn familie en vrienden, muziek volleybal, hardlopen en reizen.  Ik ben gek op het ontdekken van nieuwe plekken, zowel binnen als buiten Europa. Voor mij is deze plek de ideale plek van wonen; midden in het centrum, alles op loop- en fietsafstand. Ik ervaar hier het ultieme stadsgevoel met nog een beetje groen om mij heen! Mijn appartement bevindt zich op de topetage waardoor je de hele dag kunt genieten van een mooi uitzicht. Ik hoop dat mijn gasten zich, net als ik, ultiem thuis voelen op deze plek. Hier doe ik in ieder geval mijn uiterste best voor!

De nieuwe badkamer is voorzien van twe

name: Stylish studio near Central Station / City Centre
description:
Excellent starting point for trips in and outside the city.

Basically a one room apartment, with private bathroom and basic cooking facilities.

Located in a relatively quiet street with enough (paid) parking space (free after 6 p.m. and on sundays).

A 10 minute walk from Rotterdam CS public transport hub, concerthall De Doelen, Theater De Schouwburg and the Blijdorp ZOO.

There is a roof terrace, exclusively for the guests, with a 360° view of the city skyline.

The space
The room is about 26m2 and has an adjacent private bathroom with shower cabin and washing machine.

There are facilities to make your own thee, coffee, or simple meal.

Guest access
Guests get a key of the front door which gives acces to the communal staircases. The room is located on the fourth floor. Some guests find the stairs steep and/or narrow.

Guests have access to the communal roofterace.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbourhood was developed in the twenties and thirties of the 20th century. The street is very atmospheric with large trees and broad sidewalks, and most of the time enough parking space. On one end of the street there is a free accessable sports ground. On the other side it runs into the Heemraadssingel, a spacious area with a canal and a childrens playgroutd.
Two blocks away, the lively Middelandstraat has a multicultural atmosphere and wide range of shops, supermarkets, espressobars and lunchrooms.
host_about:
A freelance graphic and online designer, living and working In Rotterdam with Hennie and our son. 
I like the cultural offerings of the city, such as the museums, theater and cinema's.
In our holidays we like to combine culture with nature, and love to hike and bike.

name: Comfy Room @ Historical Delfshaven
description:
Modern, spacious double bedroom with lots of windows, sunny mornings in a beautiful, renovated building.
Just a 7 min. metro ride to Rotterdam centre.
Public transport,taxi,supermarkets,nightshop,drugstores,market etc are right at your doorstep.

The space
I can offer you a comfy stay in a large, beautiful, double bedroom with marble floor and 3 large windows, with a view on a lovely, lively, little square.
Our house is situated only just a two minute walk from Historical Delfshaven and close to Rotterdam Centre.
The room has a small safe, refrigerator, tv, WiFi, large table/desk, two comfortable seats with coffee table and two wardrobes .
The room is accessable by glass sliding, lockable doors (privacy guaranteed by large curtains).
You share:
- a light a light, cozy kitchen with dishwasher, microwave oven, waterboiler, Nespresso Coffee machine and a dining table for four
- a beautiful, marble bathroom with shower and toil
neighborhood_overview:
Visit the district of Delfshaven, located close to vibrant Rotterdam centre. In multicultural Delfshaven no one is an outsider. The people are relaxed and friendly.
Our house is situated on a lovely, little, lively square with benches, an organic shop and McDonalds next door. Around the corner left and right you will find drugstores, money exchange, teller machine, restaurants, pubs, hairdressers,internetcafe, nailstudio, fresh fishstore, butcher, a landromat and a large variety of other small stores.
In romantic, 16th century Historical Delfshaven, close to our house, you will find a small beerfactory, art studio's , a large poolcafé and various nice restaurants.
Across the street is a large supermarket (Jumbo, open from 08:00 - 21:00 seven days a week). On Thursday and Saturday there is a large market at a 5 minute walking distance from the apartment, where you can buy a variety of products. Across from the building there is an evening supermarket, open till midnight.
host_about:
In my free time i enjoy beeing with friends, going out and going to festivals. 
In the summer i love to travel with my old-timer camper and visit festivals in Europe.

The space
on the day of your arrival everything for a simple breakfast is ready for you in the apartment, in the mini-fridge you'll find something to drink as well.
you can find a nice selection of books, dvd's, cd's and magazines in our place; there is a lot of information about rotterdam to be found in books, maps and magazines as well.

Guest access
you can use balcony and garden, situated on the north side of the house, so not much sunshine unfortunately. the garden is not suited for (small) children, as you have to go down steep stairs to reach it.

Other things to note
a cat and a dog are living in the apartments above the b&b

Cosy little hang-out as you have never seen before. Charismatic, detailed and a whole different world you are used to. Feels like you are in a movie.

Scooter's Garage does not smell like and old garage. Please keep in mind it's newly built like a film set.

description:
Ons vakantiehuisje staat op een heel rustig plekje met veel privacy en mooie natuur. Er zijn 2 grote terassen met tuinsets waarbij je heerlijk uit de wind kunt relaxen.
Het huisje is compleet ingericht en geschikt voor 4 personen. Er staat een schuurtje met 2 grote fietsen een 3 kleine kinderfietsen en driewieler voor de allerkleinste.
Het huisje staat op het vakantiepark " Kruiningengors " onderdeel van de molencaten vakantieparken en ligt langs het Brielse meer.

The space
Het houten vakantiehuisje is rond 30m2 groot en compleet gemoderniseerd en voorzien van alle gemakken. Er is 1 slaapkamer en een grote slaapbank in de woonkamer. Een Keuken en badkamer met toilet. Recent is er een 80 liter boiler geplaatst zodat iedereen rustig kan douche. In het huisje is een kinderbedje aanwe
neighborhood_overview:
The house is situated at a holiday park 'Kruiningen Gors'. It's situated at the lake of Brielle with great outdoor options. take the bikes and njoy the historic town of Brielle with it's historic museum And harbour.
The beautifull beaches of the 'Maasvlakte' are 10 min by car with a lot of Free parkingplace or with a bike ( 7 KM).
Visit one of the most beautifull Dunes 'Voorse Duinen' by bike and go have a drink at the beaches of Rockanje, there are several Beachclubs.

The house has 2 mountainbikes, 2 citybikes and small childeren bikes You can use.

name: Special&Spacious urban family house
description:
Our special&spacious house with garden is situated in Rotterdam-West. We transformed the former 3 apartments into one spacious and modern house with special features like an industrial staircase, a monochrome blue bathroom and a ‘floating' kitchen.

The space
Our special and spacious house with garden is situated in the vibrant neighborhood of Rotterdam-West. The house is originally from the 1930’s but we recently completely renovated it ourselves. We transformed these former 3 apartments into one spacious (200 square meters) and modern family house with special features like an open industrial staircase, a monochrome blue epoxy bathroom and a ‘floating’ kitchen.
The house has four floors, a private garden and a communal garden. It consist out of a cozy kitchen (with oven, dishwasher and espresso-machine) and dining room with a table which suites 8 people, a separate toilet, a spacious living room, a master bedroom with a double bed and balcony, two children
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is part of a very special renovation project. Together with our 25 neighbors we got the houses for free from the local government and renovated them to everyones own wishes. There are a lot of creative people in our block; artists, designers and architects. The inner area of the block is a huge communal garden, making the place a green and quit oasis within the busy city.
The house is situated in the nice, vibrant neighborhood of Rotterdam-West. There are lots of shops, restaurants and coffee places in the direct area. It’s a 5-minute walk from the Van Nelle Fabriek (Unesco world heritage), which offers several events and art fairs during the year. For children there are playgrounds, a petting zoo, a park, the Blijdorp zoo and a very nice and unique ‘wild nature playground’ nearby. The stadium of the Sparta football club leis within the neighborhood; you can hear them cheer on Sunday afternoon.

name: Cute Room for Two in Amazing Historic Ship!
description:
Welcome to Avontuur - the Ark for Healing, Wellbeing and Inner Growth. A historic clipper located in the heart of the city center of Rotterdam, one of the most exciting cities in the world for travelers! Avontuur is more then just a lodging space, it is an experience. An open ashramic space that offers yoga, meditation, workshops and concerts, as well as massage, coaching and an amazing spa experience. We have three beautiful spaces available, the Cute Room, the Cozy Room, and the Captains Hut.

The space

host_about:
I am an architect, urban planner and self development trainer.

Born on the East African equator at sunrise on the first day of spring, I was raised throughout Africa, Asia and the Caribbean and have travelled to the far reaches of the world exploring different natures, cultures and spiritual teachings. 

Since 1991 I am based in the Netherlands and have taken my students of architecture and city planning to slums and natural disaster areas across the globe researching and implementing sustainable development. 

I also offer self development workshops and sessions, and run holistic retreats in the Caribbean.

My life is devoted to the betterment of the planet and its peoples. I use my mind, body and soul to support the individual and collective consciousness.

neighborhood_overview:
Rotterdam’s Central District is the gateway to the city and home to many international companies and multinationals. The area buzzes with a constant stream of people coming and going, which can make you think of New York. A hive of activity. Rotterdam Central railway station is the Central District’s new landmark.

Central railway station, Concert hall De Doelen, Theatre Stadsschouwburg and Cinema Pathé are literally around the corner on a 3 minutes walking distance.

West-Kruiskade is a long shopping street with shops representing every corner of the world, from Chinese to Surinamese shops selling everything under the sun and from Dutch butcher’s to Turkish baker’s shops. Its many multicultural restaurants and snack bars make it the ideal place to find an exotic bite to eat. The West-Kruiskade is often compared similar to the famous Zeedijk in Amsterdam.

The Museumkwartier is a dynamic area where lots of museums, art institutions and galleries are based

neighborhood_overview:
The house is centrally located in a beautiful, quiet street in the city centre of Rotterdam. It's a ideal location to explore the local neighborhood and to discover downtown Rotterdam and the rest of the city. The Nieuwe Binnenweg, the longest and most vibrant alternative shopping street of Rotterdam, runs parallel (one block north) to our street. The street is a perfect example of Rotterdam’s diversity. It features a surprising mix of original and authentic stores, local bakeries and coffee places, as well as many bar/restaurants with food from all over the world. Just around our corner are two well-stacked supermarkets (one of which organic). Also around the corner you’ll find one of the best and most relaxed coffee bars in town (Urban Espresso Bar West) and grand cafe (Westerpaviljoen), various great restaurants (Italians, Gourmet Burger, French, Surinam) and a jazz club just around the corner.

name: Cosy apartment in Rotterdam center
description:
A modern and bright 2 floors apartment in the very center of Rotterdam, close to nice bars and restaurants. The apartment is fully equiped, nicely decorated and has been recently renovated. Perfect location to explore or simply enjoy Rotterdam life!

The space
The location is perfect: 15 minutes walk from Rotterdam Central Station and a only a few steps from Witte de Withstraat, one of the coolest street in Rotterdam! Most of the main attraction from Rotterdam (Erasmus bridge, Markthal, Cubic houses...) are walking distance from the apartment. Public transport is also available around the corner.

You can use the free wifi and the TV when at home or just relax on the balcony to enjoy the sun (yes it can be sunny in Rotterdam!) A barbecue is also available on the balcony but of course be careful when using it.

In the kitchen you can find all you need: dishwasher, fridge, freezer, oven, microwave, Nespresso machine, toaster, kettle...

name: Cosy house in old barn!
description:
The barnhouse is situated in the outback of Rotterdam in an old hamlet called 'De Kandelaar'. There live only 30 people in this silent spot of nature between the (big) cities Rotterdam and Delft.

It is the perfect place to combine nature with the city!

Only 5km form the historic city Schiedam, 8km from the city Delft and 12 km form the city Rotterdam.

The house is situated in a nature resort called 'Recreactie gebied Midden Delfland'.

The space
The house is suitable for 2 persons.

On the first floor you will find the large living room with the woodstove and a large bedroom with a nice luxurious adjustable bed.

Guest access
The house has it's own main entrance, bathroom, toilet and kitchen with dishwasher, refrigerator, deep freezer and oven.

Witte de Withstraat is the place to be when visiting Rotterdam. It has many restaurants that are open till late and amazing bars with seating outside. It is a two minute walk to the nearest tube station and three minute walk to the shopping district.

Furthermore it is nearby the Coolsingel which houses the Rotterdam City hall, and it's nearby the shopping boulevard of the city. If you don't like the big shops you can also visite the small boutiques on the Van Oldenbarneveldstraat, Karel Doormanstraat or de Meent.
If you have a panache for art, local products or like to buy things from local artists, entrepreneurs, hobbyist/amateurs, the Witte de Withstraat is dotted with (vintage and pop-up) shops/boutiques & galleries that sell these.

It's a 10 minute walk from:

- the Cubic houses
- the Eramusburg where you can explor

En met alle fijne restaurantjes in de buurt, kun je heerlijk ontbijten, lunchen en dineren. Of met je picknickmand aan het water. De supermarkten en biologisch winkels zijn op geringe loopafstand. host_about:
Ik ben docent beeldende vorming en geef workshops en cursussen aan kinderen en volwassenen in eigen atelier. Ik maak zelf schilderijen in gemengde technieken.
Het atelier ligt achter het huis. Ik fiets, zwem en schaats graag, en bezoek vaak theater, film en concerten in Rotterdam e.o. Ik heb 3 dochters, die het huis uit zijn (vandaar de airbnb activiteiten). Sinds 2020 heb ik een geweldig leuke kleinzoon. 
Het huis waarin ik woon is uit 1910, wat enorm leuk is maar ook niet erg onderhoudsvriendelijk ;).

name: Great Houseboat Holiday Apartment on Ship "Mizar"
description:
This comfortable apartment is fully self catered and on an amazing ship that lies in the centre of Rotterdam. In walking distance of the Markthal, Coolsingel, Koopgoot and Erasmusbrug. Enjoy everything that Rotterdam has to offer. Look for me on Social Media use @ HouseboatRotterdam. I share tips and nice pictures there.

The space
This Ship, a Spits, was build in 1937. It was used to carry goods over the Dutch rivers. In 2009 the biggest part of the Ship, the cargo hold, was fully renovated and made into accommodation for guests to stay in. This means that the space is clean and comfortable, and at the same time you still feel that you're on a ship. Rotterdam, being an seaport, is connected to the sea. This means that the ship moves with the tides. The difference is 2 meters, so it's possible you go into town and have to climb the walkway while leaving the ship and when you come back you have to climb the walkway again while entering the ship.

Gues
neighborhood_overview: Rotterdam is an amazing city with interesting architecture, nice restaurants and bars and of course the harbor that gives it its international allure. The best part of the location of the ship is that it's in the city centre. That means you can walk to all Points of interest. The most bustling and vibrant street of the city with wonderful bars and restaurants, the Witte de Withstraat is visible from the ship.
host_about:
I'm born in Holland and currently live in Rotterdam. I studied Law and Medieval History in Groningen. I have worked in Knowledge Management in big Lawyers firms for about 15 years and currently coordinate Tenders for an IT Company. In february 2017 I moved from a small, 40 sqm, houseboat in the beautiful old centre of Amsterdam to my beautiful 200 sqm ship in the centre of Rotterdam. The ship was already divided in 3 apartments and I moved in the one in the middle of the ship. The apartment in the front I now rent to guests who want to explore Rotterdam and make their stay extra special by sleeping on a ship. 
I speak English and German fluently and understand Italian and French. I love to receive guests from all over the world and share my excitement about this vibrant City of Rotterdam.

Light studio appartement with sunny garden. The neighbourhood is known for it's many artists and has a very old (1800's) centre. The Maastunnel will take you 10 minutes on bicycle to historic Delfshaven and 15 minutes to the city centre of Rotterdam. Take the Ferry to Katendrecht (6 minutes) and you will find yourself in the urban industrial part of the city with many restaurants, bars and indoor fresh food market.
The ‘Zuiderpark’ is at walking distance and grocery shops are around the corner.

The space
Spacious studio apartment with very high ceiling. Nice and cool in the summer, cosy in the winter. Flatscreen with USB connection. Wireless connection (Chromecast) between your phone/ iPad and television to watch Netflix or YouTube for example. Rain-shower, separate toilet.

Guest access

neighborhood_overview:
Close to Ahoy, the Classic cruise ship ‘SS Rotterdam’, University Hospital Erasmus, Katendrecht (visit Fenix Food hall and try the craft beers of our city brewery ‘Kaapse Brouwers’), historic Delfshaven, Euromast.

The ‘Kralingse plas en bos’ (large lake and forest in the city) is 35minutes on bike and great to rent a boat or SUP.

If you like nature, visit the Biesbosch. A ferry takes you along the Maas river to Dordrecht. A quicker option is by bike and train. You can hire a boat or kayak to experience this beautiful area.
I can provide you all the info you need when you are here.

The studio will make you feel home away from home <3

If you have a panache for art, local products or like to buy things from local artists, entrepreneurs, hobbyist/amateurs, the Witte de Withstraat is dotted with (vintage and pop-up) shops/boutiques & galleries that sell these.

- the Cubic houses
- the Eramusburg where you can explor

name: Central 350m2/ 6p river side design apartment
description:
This design apartment on the Maas quay is unique because of its location and design. Everything shows that it was renovated under the supervision of an interior architect. The 4 meter high ceilings and the enormous surface of 350m2 make this house feel very spacious.

Located in the center and historic district Delfshaven, there are many attractions within walking distance. Because the metro and tram stops are close to the house, the rest of Rotterdam is also quickly and easily accessible.

The space
This old Industrial building has recently been completly renovated under supervision of an interior architect. In front of the house is a conservatory with a view on the Maas river. Enjoy a nice glass of wine here and watch the ships passing by.

In the residential part of the house there is a spacious office / library and a very spacious and well-equipped kitchen. Central to the room is the large cozy dining table and in the back by the fireplace
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located on the quay of the Maas river in the historical Delfshaven district. Only 20 minutes from Central Station. There are many good and cozy restaurants in this neighborhood. Within walking distance is the old marina. In the old canal houses you can now find antique and curio shops, small distilleries, restaurants and some craft beer breweries.

Because this house is close to several tram stops and a metro stop, the rest of the city is well connected by public transport. You can be at the Museumpark in 10 minutes, at the Maritime museum in 15 minutes and at the boarding point for the boat trips in about 20 minutes.

The "Nieuwe Binnenweg", known for its many nice boutique shops, is only 10 minutes by metro and the Witte de With, the entertainment street with lively bars and many restaurants, is only 12 minutes away.

name: CHEZ ALET, Rotterdam centrum, Delfshaven
description:
Op 6 minuten lopen is mooi en rustig, historisch Delfshaven.
Leuk om te eten en drinken.
Looproutes naar centrum kan ik aanbevelen en goed bereikbaar met het openbaar vervoer.
Mijn appartement is, gerenoveerd, vintage ingericht met uitzicht op het Schie-kanaal.
Indeling: woonkamer, eetkamer, 2 slaapkamers, 1 slaapkamer met zeer goed twee persoons- (M-line matras) bed, 1 slaapkamer met stapelbed, volledig uitgeruste keuken, wasmachine, badkamer/toilet televisie en een balkon.

The space
Mijn ruime, lichte en sfeervol ingerichte appartement is voorzien van alle moderne gemakken.
Het uitzicht op de Schie, een druk bevaard kanaal tussen de Rotterdamse haven en Delft geeft u het gevoel echt in havenstad Rotterdam te zijn.
Het is heerlijk om naar buiten te kijken. En het is zeer eenvoudig om bv. s'avonds nog even een wandelingetje te maken en een drankje te drinken.

Zie ook CHEZ ALET inst gram.

Guest access
neighborhood_overview:
Als u geïnteresseerd bent, beveel ik u t.z.t een app aan met diverse wandelroutes in Rotterdam met informatie onderweg. Het is een stadswandeling zonder gids op uw eigen tempo, tijd en gratis.

In de omgeving zijn meerder gezellige winkels, restaurantjes, cafés en bezienswaardigheden.
Op 500 meter ligt historisch Delfshaven, een authentiek stukje Rotterdam, met o.a. de Pelgrimskerk, waar de "Pilgrims fathers" in 1620 naar de "nieuwe wereld' zijn vertrokken. In de U.S. nog steeds een begrip.
De bekende zeeheld Piet Hein heeft zijn sporen achtergelaten in deze omgeving.
In Delfshaven liggen bewoonde platbodems en het staat bekend om de pittoreske gevels. Verder is hier stadsbrouwerij de Pelgrim gevestigd.
De Euromast en "Het park" liggen op 1,5 km afstand van het appartement. Dit is een leuke wandeling langs de Schie en brengt u naar de Nieuwe Maas. Waar de Haven van Rotterdam zichtbaar wordt.
In deze omgeving zijn er veel toeristische attractie
host_about:
Hallo,
Als ik thuis ben en mijn koffie drink kijk ik graag naar de vrachtschepen die voorbij varen. Dit geeft mij het gevoel in een havenstad te wonen.
Ik maak graag wandelingen door de stad en drink mijn biertje in toeristisch Delfshaven wat 5 min lopen van mijn huis ligt. 
Hier ligt veel geschiedenis van de stad. Vanuit deze plek is Rotterdam min of meer uitgebouwd. Het is daar rustig en mooi. Het lijkt een beetje op Amsterdam met zijn grachten en pakhuiswoningen.

Ik ben een creatief persoon en ben graag fysiek bezig.
In mijn B&B zul je de sfeer van creativiteit kunnen proeven.
De inrichting van heel mijn huis heb ik in de stijl van het huis wat in 1924 gebouwd is. Bovendien is het een bewuste keuze om te recycelen.

Naast mijn benb vind ik het heerlijk om in mijn tuin te tuinieren.  Ik schilder graag en maak tassen. 
Ik help anderen hun huis te reorganiseren en opknappen.
Dus u zou mij in kluskleding aan kunnen treffen ;-)

Sinds kort bezit ik een camperbusje. Ik ben daar erg blij mee en ga graag naar natuulijke campings waar het vaak mooi, rustig en vriendelijk is. Bovendien is daar qua natuur veel te beleven.

name: Characteristic house in lush Kralingen
description:
This unique, modern and luxurious apartment has everything you need and more… much more! Everything in this high-end apartment is designed to fit your every need while enjoying Rotterdam. A lot of comfort can be enjoyed in the house during your stay because of the comfortable bed and living spaces as well as the balcony. The amount of windows provide beautiful light throughout the whole house.

You will find shops, eatery's and cozy restaurants all within walking distance.

The space
Wake up with an amazing view of the Dutch lane or enjoy your morning coffee on this sunny balcony before leaving for some sightseeing.

The fully equipped kitchen has everything you need to cook yourself a chef-worthy dinner, lunch or breakfast. Don't feel like cooking? Treat yourself on a nice bite to eat or drink in one of the local restaurants or bars.

We've got 1 Kingsize bed for you to get your well earned rest, after a long day in our magnificent c
neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is traditionally known as the chiquer side of Rotterdam. Romantic villa neighbourhoods and elegant lanes dominate the cityscape here. Erasmus University Rotterdam is also located here, however, so the area is home to lots of students – and they keep Kralingen lively! Oostzeedijk boasts lots of popular pubs and restaurants where you can pick up a meal for a reasonable price. One of the oldest attractions in Kralingen is Arboretum Trompenburg. In addition to the lovely old trees here, these botanic gardens offer beautiful plants and flowers and a charming teahouse.

The biggest park in Rotterdam is nearby: the Kralingse Bos, a green oasis for everyone hoping to escape the city for a breath of fresh air and some peace and quiet. Visitors rollerblade, jog and cycle around the lake to their heart’s content. Sailboats skim across the lake, while tasty snacks are served at sidewalk cafés along the waterfront.
host_about:
Hi! My name is Renee, an energetic and positive woman, and I want to welcome you in my urban meets industry house in one of the most vibrant cities of the world. Rotterdam is my hometown and I love to tell you about my favorites local spots and the culture of Rotterdam.
I was born and raised in Rotterdam and I working in the sales department of our shipyard in Rotterdam, so I can tell you all about it!

Furthermore it is nearby the Coolsingel which houses the Rotterdam City hall, and it's nearby the shopping boulevard of the city. If you don't like the big shops you can also visite the small boutiques on the Van Oldenbarneveldstraat, Karel Doormanstraat or de Meent.
If you have a panache for art, local products or like to buy things from local artists, entrepreneurs, hobbyist/amateurs, the Witte de Withstraat is dotted with (vintage and pop-up) shops/boutiques & galleries that sell these.

It's a 10 minute walk from:
- the newly constructed Markthal, which you really should visite to buy some local products or eat something at the venues.
- the Cubic houses

description:

The space

host_location: Krimpen aan den IJssel, South Holland, Netherlands
host_about:
Wij stellen ons graag even aan u voor.

Wij een ondernemers familie uit de omgeving van Rotterdam en in 2003 is Kick ons team komen versterken.

Als er een kind in je gezin komt wordt alles anders, vooral het op vakantie gaan. Je moet ineens rekening met alles houden, niet te warm, niet te koud, kinderbadje, tussen de middag slapen, kinderbedje, geen stijl in zee lopend strand, geen rotsen, geen hoge golven... en als de kinderen ouder worden; vermaken zij zich wel? Is er genoeg te doen? Zijn er wel vriendjes? Is er wel eten wat ze lusten?

Wij hebben de eerste jaren daar wel mee geworsteld, want je wilt het zelf ook naar je zin hebben op vakantie... je moet immers je het hele jaar al wegcijferen.

Onze vakantie ervaringen:

We zijn naar een resort in Turkije geweest...
Wij vonden het veel te massaal, heel de dag door buffetten en te ver buiten het stadje. Alle resorts staan in de middle of nowhere zodat je alles binnen het complex moet doen. En niet te vergeten het onvermijdelijke animatie-team die iedere avond een toneelstukje opvoert.

We zijn naar het "kindvriendelijke" Menorca geweest...
Het begon met een overstap op Ibiza (vliegtuig vol Ibiza-gangers die zich doodergeren aan de kinderen), geen strand (moerassig), onverwarmd zwembad (steenkoud) en saai... Het is niet kindvriendelijk..., er zijn alleen heel veel kinderen!

We zijn naar Tenerife (en alle andere Canarische eilanden) geweest...
Na onze ervaringen in Turkije en Menorca wilden we graag een hotel aan een boulevard zodat we 's avonds nog wat konden lopen en wat drinken...het hotel was schitterend, maar zodra je de boulevard op kwam... wat een armoe! Straten kapot, veel leegstand in de winkelruimtes, overal schreeuwende aanbiedingen voor een pint bier voor € 1,-

We zijn naar Club Med geweest (Tunesie en Turkije)...
Slechte accomodaties, wel goed publiek maar het concept dat het personeel  iedere keer bij je aan tafel komt zitten sprak ons niet zo aan.

Toen dachten we, als we nu eens een eigen huis huren met een zwembad in Spanje..., maar waar? Na wat ge (Hidden by Airbnb) kwamen we uit bij Moraira! Dit sprak ons meteen aan... authentiek, geen hoogbouw, niet te toeristisch, vissersplaatsje, jachthaven, veel winkeltjes, restaurantjes en terrassen, zandstrand, in een baai, strand loopt niet stijl in zee, altijd zon (320 dagen van het jaar), nagenoeg geen regen, goede temperatuur, genoeg vermaak in de buurt voor jong en oud, tennisbanen (ons zoontje tennist veel en graag), kortom dit moest het zijn!

Al deze informatie vonden we op de site van Xenofilia, twee Nederlandse broers die vakantiehuizen verhuren en er zelf ook wonen. Een groot huis, Xenofilia I... 4 kamers, 4 badkamers, verwarmd zwembad en een eigen tennisbaan... Dit is het!

Alle opa's en oma's mee en met z'n zevenen naar Spanje. We hebben een geweldige vakantie gehad, en van het plaatsje Moraira was niets gelogen, helmaal naar ons zin! Alles is er luxe afgewerkt, de straten, het meubilair, schitterende rotondes met kunstwerken. Wij hebben echt wel veel gezien, maar dit was fantastisch! Je zou dan aan st. Tropez prijzen gaan denken...niets is minder waar, een wijntje op het strand kost € 2,- en het eten in de restaurantjes en op de terrassen is zeker niet duurder dan in Nederland.

Inmiddels zijn we zo'n 15 keer terug geweest, nog een paar keer in Xenofilia I zonder opa's en oma's maar met een vriendje voor Kick.

Het enige nadeel van een huis is dat je alles met de auto moet doen... boodschappen, naar het strand en de kinderen zitten een beetje opgesloten in en om het huis. Dus, hebben we de laatste paar keren een appartement in het centrum gehuurd. Zo kon onze zoon, inmiddels 11, gewoon zelf naar het strand en weer terug naar het appartement. Ook hoefden we nu geen vriendje meer mee te nemen, er zijn genoeg kinderen op het strand, en daar is altijd zat te doen... Voetballen, volleyballen, vissen, krabbetjes zoeken, snorkelen, tegen de branding in springen en natuurlijk zwemmen. Wij vinden het lekker om als we van het strand komen op het balkon lekker een wijntje te drinken en wat tappaatjes te eten. Daar vind Kick natuurlijk geen bal aan en hij vindt tappas niet lekker. Hij gaat dan een pizza voor zichzelf halen bij de pizzaria 100 meter verder en gaat lekker even op zijn iPad een spelletje spelen. Iedereen blij! 

Wij zijn ook een keer in januari gegaan, en in de voorjaarsvakantie... hoe zou het dan zijn? Nou, ook gewoon 20 graden en zonnig en totaal niet uitgestorven!

Moeten we dan niet kijken of we hier wat kunnen kopen? Maar we hebben zelf geen tijd om vaak te gaan... kunnen we het dan niet verhuren als we zelf niet gaan?

De rest is geschiedenis... dus kom genieten van dit pareltje aan de Costa Blanca en geniet van ons luxe appartement. 

Welkom!

Robert, Joyce en Kick

neighborhood_overview:
You live in blijdoorp (translated: happy village); a lush, authentic & dynamic neighborhood behind the city center.
Here you find several restaurants, pubs, supermarkets & everything you might occasionally need. With only 10 minutes walking distance from the city centre & Rotterdam's central station, so you have all the options. You can easily jump on a train to explore other beautiful dutch cities Utrecht, Amsterdam or Den Hague, or even go to the beach at Hook van Holland...
The house opens to a beautiful view. Where there used to be a monestry garden, there is now a small neighbourhood tennis court, surrounded by big trees. If it wasn't for the tiny bit of skyline, you would almost forget that you are in the city with the biggest haven in Europe!

description:
An amazing, light and sunny apartment on the sixth floor of the popular Timmerhuis building, with nice views over the city skyline.

The apartment has two terraces, both of 45m2, one on the east side and the other on the south/west side, both with trees and plants. There are two sunbeds and two lounge chairs.

The space

The bathroom has both a bathtub and a shower.

The apartment is equipped with underfloor heating, which in the summer can also be used aa cooling.

neighborhood_overview:
Located in the heart of the city, just behind the City hall.

Shopping areas, restaurants and bars are just around the corner. All major sight seeings are within walking distance.

host_about:
Hi, 

I am Saskia, single, lawyer. I have been living and working in Rotterdam for about 30 years. In July 2015 I bought the apartment in the Timmerhuis (casco), and I moved in at the end of 2015. 
I live there with a lot of pleasure! The location is fantastic, I have very nice neighbors and the apartment itself has everything I could want. But the terraces are my pride and joy, and also the main reason for buying the apartment. I have what you call in Dutch "green fingers."

Because of a major leak, which fortunately has now been fixed, I was unable to accept bookings for a year.  This was followed by the Covid pandemic. 

I look forward to hearing your experiences! 

Greetings, 
Saskia

host_about: I have been living in Rotterdam for 25 years. I live with my daughter Isa (2009) in our cute little house, we’re in the north of the city (the area called: ‘Liskwartier’). I absolutely love this city and know it very well. I’m the no-nonense type of person. I love traveling, meeting people, trying new things, eating, friends, good Coffee, being outside, in and on the water, surfing, art, design and culture. I’m running a mobile catering (kitchen build in a oldtimer truck) were I’m also the chef. I mostly work on filmsets all cross the country, cooking from my mobile kitchen for the crew. I work hard, but I work to live, not live to work.

name: Authentic City App. with peaceful garden.
description:
Spacious and comfortable ground floor apartment including beautiful garden.
You will have a great stay in this characteristic over 100 years old mansion in the heart of the city only 900 meters from the central station, with lot's of cafes, terraces, galleries, restaurants and shops surrounding you.

The space
The house is over 100 years old so it has lots of character and with the comfort of modern day standards. It is situated on the ground floor and has its own entrance. The long hallway will give you access to all the spaces and rooms in the house. There is nothing shared, so you will have your privacy and comfort. The apartment is about 80 m2. It offers all necessary utilities such as bathroom, toilet, kitchen, living room and bedroom en suite. The style and character is used throughout the entire apartment.
Free wifi is available.
The kitchen contains an Illy coffee machine and offcourse an electric water cooker.
The living room has bea
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in a very nice neighborhood behind Central Station. The station is about 900 meters walk and there you will find yourself in the hart of Rotterdam which offers the nicest cafes, restaurants, museums, galleries, shops and cinemas, the museum park with Museum Boymans and De Kunsthal, the authentic Witte the Withstraat, the Binnenweg, China Town with several small toko's is all within walking distance.

Exploring the city by electric scooter is the best way.
With the electric scooter you can go to the nearby parks such as Vroesenpark and off course a "must see" Kralingse Bos. You can go to the center or take a walk along the river Maas, cross the Erasmus bridge and go by watertaxi to different parts of the city.

With public transportation nearby you can reach all different parts of the city with their own charme and character.
Public transport is nearby with tram around the corner and a subway station within 5 minutes walk.
host_about:
Hi, my name is Harald and I live in the beautiful and upcoming city of Rotterdam. I love to travel and discover the world. But coming home after another adventure always brings a smile to my face. This is because this city is my home and my home is my sanctuary. I appreciate and enjoy it a lot and I hope you will too.
Life is short, so enjoy as much as you can!

On the corner of the street you will find your groceries, drugstore, florists and fun boutiques.  Across the street is a professional Beauty Bar where you can get a massage, solarium, or your nails done. One block away you can even get pierced or tattooed...! host_about:
Hi there!

Next to one of the old spice mills "De Ster", you’ll find the former miller’s house, which has been redeveloped into two luxurious heritage studios at the lakeside (Ground floor studio & First Floor studio).

The space
Heritage lodge "De Karot" (35m2) is located on the first floor of the former miller's house. The lodge, with a magnificent view on the lake, is split into 2 independent units, both with their own private entrance. You can also rent both units (the units are connected with a locked and soundproof door).

The living area has a sofa bed (fits for two children or one adult), a small, but well-equipped (dining) kitchen and a glass door displaying windmill "De Ster". The studio has a small private terrace on the lake (see photo). The entrance to the
neighborhood_overview:
The heritage lodges are situated in the middle of the Kralingse Bos (forest), a green oasis in the heart of the city of Rotterdam.

Right next to the lodge you’ll find a nice restaurant which offers breakfast, lunch and dinner. The Kralingse Bos is a wonderful recreational area with all sorts of things to do. There’s for example a small beach, a sailing school, petting zoo, deer park, golf club and climbing park. And if you feel like popping into town, the centre of Rotterdam is just 3 metro stops away.

name: Culture Campsite - Sleeping Pod
description:
Spending the night at this sustainable campsite is a guarantee for the most special night's sleep you've ever had. You'll sleep in one of the various small-scale architectural objects between fragrant plants in less than ten minutes from the city centre of Rotterdam and a stone's throw from the river the Maas. The sleeping objects are smaller than a tiny house, more exciting than a tent and different from all glamping accommodations. On the campsite are sanitary facilities and a common room.

The space
This sleeping object is called Sleeping Pod. It is made of discarded materials. What served as shelters for cattle has now been transformed into a small multi-use space. "I have a Swedish name which means walrus but I come from the countryside of the Netherlands."

name: Modern and cozy central apartment
description:
This is a modern and cozy apartment, which is perfect for one or two people coming to Rotterdam for work or pleasure. The area is just a few minutes away from the city centre and is well connected to restaurants and shops. The apartment has got anything you need for a pleasant and resting stay. If you also like to cook or chill with your friends enjoying a glass of wine, I am sure you will immediately feel at home here!
Please contact me for any information -- great local tips included!

The space
The apartment is located in a historical building, which is quite rare in a city like Rotterdam! The living area is lit by two big windows on opposite sites: perfect to enjoy a cozy breakfast or an aperitif with natural light.

name: Luxurious heritage lodge at lakeside - Studio 1/2
description:
Studio 1/2

Next to one of the old spice mills "De Ster", you’ll find the former miller’s house, which has been redeveloped into two luxurious heritage studios at the lakeside (Ground floor studio & First Floor studio).

The space
Heritage lodge "De Ster" (45m2) is located on the ground floor of the former miller's house. The lodge, with a magnificent view on the lake, is split into 2 independent units, both with their own private entrance. You can also rent both units (the units are connected with a locked and soundproof door).

The sitting area has a nice fireplace and is connected to a small, but well-equipped (dining) kitchen. The spacious bedroom has a double Auping bed, a small sofa bed (fits for two children or one adult), a freestanding bathtub and a separate bathroom with floor heating, shower and sink. The studio has a separate toilet and a private terrace on the lake. The entrance to the studio is at the rear and has his own (free)
neighborhood_overview:
The heritage lodges are situated in the middle of the Kralingse Bos (forest), a green oasis in the heart of the city of Rotterdam.

Right next to the lodge you’ll find a nice restaurant which offers breakfast, lunch and dinner. The Kralingse Bos is a wonderful recreational area with all sorts of things to do. There’s for example a small beach, a sailing school, petting zoo, deer park, golf club and climbing park. And if you feel like popping into town, the centre of Rotterdam is just 3 metro stops away.

The apartment is a 5 minute walk from the Central Station and a 10 minute walk from the center. The square where the apartment is situated is a green oase in the best town in Holland with several restaurants just around the corner. Breakfast is inclusive.

The bedroom, of 15 m2 has a 140x200 cm bed, a big wardrobe and a breakfast table and two chairs. It is situated in an apartment on the ground (only 7 steps higher then street level) floor where I, Brigitte, your host, also live. With me and possibly one or two other guests you share the kitchen, toilet and bathroom. The living room is private.

De kamer is in een heerlijk licht huis..met heel veel ruimte! De kamer heeft een plafond uit 1790, die geschilderd is door reizende schilders. Uniek en je zult deze ervaring nergens anders krijgen! Verder is de kamer zeer ruim en licht en heeft de kamer toegang tot de patio.

name: Culture Campsite - Musca Domestica
description:
Spending the night at this sustainable campsite is a guarantee for the most special night's sleep you've ever had. You'll sleep in one of the various small-scale architectural objects between fragrant plants in less than ten minutes from the city centre of Rotterdam and a stone's throw from the river the Maas. The sleeping objects are smaller than a tiny house, more exciting than a tent and different from all glamping accommodations. On the campsite are sanitary facilities and a common room.

The space
“Do you always know what you see?” You will initially see a normal brick wall, our brain fills in the missing pieces. However, as you get closer, no stone seems to touch the other. Every stone floats in the air, but together they form a solid brick wall. Floating Bricks combines two residual flows; glass plates and rejected brick slips. Designed by ROFFAA architects.

You can also check out our other objects at culturecampsite.com

Guest acces
neighborhood_overview: Culture Campsite is located less than ten minutes from the city centre of Rotterdam and a stone's throw away from the river the Maas. Next door you'll find a restaurant and in the vicinity you will find various art places, museums, shops, restaurants and nightlife.
host_about:
We are Isis Hoos, Laura Abbink, Thijs Masthoff and Boris Duijneveld.
Together we started Culture Campsite to give people the opportunity to sleep in an original architectural or artistic object. We all studied at the art academy, focusing on autonomous arts or architectural design.

Meanwhile, 'De Hofbogen' has been restored and there are several bars and restaurants represented. The Hofbogen run along the apartment.

The space
The apartment is about 70m2 and arranged as follows: a bedroom with a double bed, a bathroom with shower unit and washing and drying machine, a separate toilet, a kitchen, a dining room/working space and living room with access to the balcony. During your stay, you may use the Wireless Internet, a part of the refrigerator and freezer, the Nespresso machine, electric kettle, toaster, oven/microwave and induction cooker. Including use of bed linen and towels.

It’s situated on the first floor and accesible by elevator or stairs. You may use my private parkingsp
neighborhood_overview:
The story of the city, the bombardment and reconstruction, and the drive to innovate that locals still use today to shape their city all make Rotterdam a fascinating place to visit. Everything seems possible here, and there’s so much left to explore. Rotterdam is a young, dynamic global city, continuously renewing itself at a rapid rate. Sparkling skyscrapers, an impressive port, trendy restaurants and food markets, renowned museums and awesome festivals are the direct result of the can-do mentality of the Rotterdammers. Add to that the many extraordinary attractions and city tours – by bike, bus, boat or on foot – and you understand why Rotterdam was voted Lonely Planet’s Best In Travel 2016.
There are some flyers in the apartment, but visit Rotterdam Tourist Information at the Coolsingel and rotterdam.info to prepare your visit to Rotterdam.
host_about:
Hi! Ik ben Olga! 
Werkzaam als docent van jongeren met gedragsproblematiek en/of een verstandelijke beperking. Ik hou van reizen (met name citytrips of fly/drives), koken en de natuur! Meestal gebruik makend van airbnb, vanwege de bijzondere plekjes i.p.v. de massa hotels en parken! Ik ben een echt stadsmens en werk ook middenin de stad, maar vertrek wanneer mogelijk naar mijn buitenhuisje in de natuur. Op die momenten verhuur ik mijn appartement aan max 2 mensen die van de mooie stad Rotterdam willen genieten en vanuit mijn appartement de stad te voet kunnen of willen verkennen.

Hi! My name is Olga!
I am a teacher, but I also work as a coach for young individuals with an intellectual disability or behavioral issues. I love traveling, most of the time citytrips or fly/drives, cooking and nature! I don’t like the big hotels with loudy tourist, so normally I book nice and special places by Airbnb! I really love living in the city and also work in the center, but in weekends I often leave to my small house a few miles away in nature. When I leave, I like to rent my apartment to max 2 people who want to enjoy the lovely city of Rotterdam!
